<br>
the belts I have seen (and not won by the way) dropped from the 4-arm guys who were pulled from the fort (#1 on the map). <br>
<br>
Centi weapons tend to drop from the toilers near the lake (#2). Never seen them drop from a toiler from another area, they might.<br>
<br>
shrouded boots and grodan idols tend to drop from the coterie at #3 (the one closest to the zone to dawnshroud).<br>
<br>
shrouded medallion from 2-arms between lake and umbral plains zone.<br>
<br>
The rarer gorangas tend to drop the nicer weapons and armor: spiritseer, chieftain, battlemaster, savant. Those are rare pops where any goranga can pop (from what I can figure).<br>
<br>
The best place for fear kiting is near the rock and tree just to the south of the zone to dawnshroud. Quad kiting is not advised in this zone due to the traps and roaming mobs. <br>
<br>
succor lands you just south of the big tree, due east of the zone to dawnshroud (wanderers WILL path through the spot).<br>
<br>
undead mobs:<br>
coteries, Xi mobs (2-arms, and are either a cleric or shadowknight), wolfshaped mobs, bats, skeletons<br>
<br>
non-undead mobs:<br>
gorangas, worms, toilers, Xin (4-arms)<br>
<br>
traps: usually pop a worm, sometimes bats or skeletons too. <p><a href='http://www.magelo.com/eq_view_profile.html?num=64195'>Combat Profile</a><br>
